# CHIP-8 / SCHIP / XO-CHIP ROM files are raw binary — never normalize line
# endings on checkout. Without this, Windows git (core.autocrlf=true) rewrites
# any 0x0A byte to 0x0D 0x0A, which corrupts the ROM and breaks chip-8-database
# SHA-1 lookups (so ROM colors / keys / tickrate never apply).
*.ch8 binary
*.rom binary

# Reference framebuffers and other binary fixtures used by the verification
# harness — same reason.
*.bin binary
